his domain using Python. The main things to learn in the book are the concept of scientific workflow, managing scientific workflow data and performing computation on this data using Python.</p>\n<p>The book discusses NumPy, SciPy, SymPy, matplotlib, Pandas and IPython with several example programs.</p>\n<p>Style and approach </p>\n<p>This book follows a hands-on approach to explain the complex concepts related to scientific computing. It details various APIs using appropriate examples.</p></div>"
